gomodel:SYNGO_192  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Voltage clamp experiments in the Calyx of Held using the specific blocker for Kv1.2 TsTX-Kalpha. Note that in this study the Kv1.2 channels are presynaptically very close to but not in the Calyx terminal.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has voltage-gated ion channel activity and is localized in teh presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'voltage-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099508)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P63142] SyNGO ID 183 (PMID:14614103, confocal). Experimental description: MM: p.28: Cochlear nucleus and brainstem slices (100-150 mm thick) were prepared as previously described (Rusznak et al. 1997; Dodson et al. 2002). 8-14 day old Wistar and Lister Hooded rats were killed by decapitation in accordance with the UK Animals -- Highlighted 15 Feb 2017" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_192" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

